name: Twilio
description: Add a Twilio Instance to connect your existing Twilio account to the Messaging Hub, allowing you to send, receive and manage email, MMS, and SMS messages etc. across multiple Messaging Elements. You will need your Twilio account information, or use our trial account to add an instance.

configuration.name: Create the Instance using Test Credentials
configuration.description: Pick true to connect to Twilio's Test  services. You will need your test credentials to authenticate

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Phone Number
configuration.description: default from phone number to use

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", ???idField???: ???user.id???, ???datesConfiguration???: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", ???createdDateField???: ???user.created_at???, ???createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }
configuration.defaultValue: {"messages":{"url":"/hubs/messaging/messages?where=DateSent='${date:yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssXXX}'","idField":"sid"},"accounts":{"url":"/hubs/messaging/accounts?where=date_updated='${gmtDate:EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z}'","idField":"sid","datesConfiguration":{"updatedDateField":"date_updated","updatedDateFormat":"EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z","updatedDateTimezone":"GMT","createdDateField":"date_created","createdDateFormat":"EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z","createdDateTimezone":"GMT"}}}

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description: Retrieve the details for sent messages from the messaging service.  Results can be filtered using a variety of search parameters, such as searching by message text.  A valid User Secret and Element Token are required in the HTTP request.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Available query terms are To, From, and DateSent. For example, to search for messages last sent on 'Jan 15, 2016', the search expression will be where=DateSent='2016-01-15'.

account_sid.description: The 34 character unique id of the Messaging Service you want to associate with this Message. Set this parameter to use the Messaging Service Settings and Copilot Features you have configured. When only this parameter is set, Twilio will use your enabled Copilot Features to select the From phone number for delivery.

api_version.description: The version of the Twilio API used to process the message.

body.description: The text body of the message. Up to 1600 characters long.

date_created.mask: EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z

date_sent.description: The date that the message was sent. For outgoing messages, this is the date that the message was sent from Twilio's platform. For incoming messages, this is the date that Twilio made the HTTP request to your application. The date is given in RFC 2822 format.
date_sent.mask: EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z

date_updated.description: The date that this resource was last updated, given in RFC 2822 format.
date_updated.mask: EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z

direction.description: The direction of this message. inbound for incoming messages, outbound-api for messages initiated via the REST API, outbound-call for messages initiated during a call or outbound-reply for messages initiated in response to an incoming message.

error_code.description: The error code, if any, associated with your message. If your message status is failed or undelivered, the ErrorCode can give you more information about the failure. The value will be null if the message was delivered successfully.

error_message.description: The human readable description of the ErrorCode above. If the message status is failed or undelivered it will have one of the values described below, otherwise, it will be null.
enum: Channel could not authenticate the request
Channel could not find From address

Channel did not accept given content
Could not format given content for the channel
Could not find request From address
Could not execute the request because the channel module has been misconfigured

from.description: The phone number or Channel address that sent this message.

num_media.description: This property indicates the number of media files associated with the message. Each message may send up to 10 media files.

num_segments.description: This property indicates the number of segments that make up the message. If your body is too large to be sent as a single SMS message, it will be segmented and charged accordingly. Inbound message over 160 characters will be reassembled when the message is received.

price.description: The amount billed for the message, in the currency associated with the account. Note that your account will be charged for each segment sent to the handset.

price_unit.description: The currency in which Price is measured, in ISO 4127 format (e.g. usd, eur, jpy).

sid.description: A 34 character unique identifier for the message. May be used to later retrieve this message from the REST API.

status.description: The status of this message. Either accepted, queued, sending, sent,failed, delivered, undelivered, receiving or received. See detailed descriptions of these statuses below.

MaxPrice.description: The total maximum price up to the fourth decimal (0.0001) in US dollars acceptable for the message to be delivered. All messages regardless of the price point will be queued for delivery. A POST request will later be made to your Status Callback URL with a status change of 'Sent' or 'Failed'. When the price of the message is above this value the message will fail and not be sent. When MaxPrice is not set, all prices for the message is accepted.

MediaUrl.description: The URL of the media you wish to send out with the message. gif , png and jpeg content is currently supported and will be formatted correctly on the recipient's device. Other types are also accepted by the API. The media size limit is 5MB. If you wish to send more than one image in the message body, please provide multiple MediaUrls values in the POST request. You may include up to 10 MediaUrls per message.
MediaUrl.x-conditional-required: Must POST atleast one of Body and MediaUrl.

StatusCallback.description: A URL where Twilio will POST each time your message status changes to one of the following: queued, failed, sent, delivered, or undelivered. Twilio will POST the MessageSid along with the other standard request parameters as well as MessageStatus and ErrorCode. If this parameter passed in addition to a MessagingServiceSid, Twilio will override the Status Callback URL of the Messaging Service. URLs must contain a valid hostname (underscores are not allowed).

resources.description: Find available phone numbers by type.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Available query terms are Contains, SmsEnabled, MmsEnabled, VoiceEnabledExcludeAllAddressRequired, ExcludeLocalAddressRequired, ExcludeForeignAddressRequired, and Beta. For example, to search for numbers containing a pattern, the search expression will be where=Contains='866***EPIC'. Valid characters for Contains are '*' and [0-9a-zA-Z]. The '*' character will match any single digit.

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: The type or region of phone numbers to search for availability. Available options are: Local, TollFree, Mobile.

parameters.name: countryCode
parameters.description: Country code of phone numbers to search for availability of.

resources.description: Create a new phone number with an available number found from GET /numbers.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: Request body. Required fields are either PhoneNumber(format: +15105555555) to reserve a specific available number OR three digit AreaCode (US and CA only) to reserve an available random number within the given AreaCode

resources.description: Ping the Element to confirm that the Hub element has a heartbeat. If the Element does not have a heartbeat, an error message will be returned.\n

Retrieve the usage data for this element.  Results can be returned using a variety of parameters such as, number of usage days.  A valid User Secret and Element Token are required in the HTTP request.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. Available query terms are Category, StartDate, and EndDate. For example, to get the total price of all usage to the account, the search expression will be where=Category='totalprice'.

all_time.description: Return a single UsageRecord for each usage category, each representing usage over the date-range specified. This is the same as the root /Usage/Records.

daily.description: Return multiple UsageRecords for each usage category, each representing usage over a daily time-interval.

last_month.description: Return a single UsageRecord per usage category, for last month's usage only.

monthly.description: Return multiple UsageRecords for each usage category, each representing usage over a monthly time-interval.

this_month.description: Return a single UsageRecord per usage category, for this month's usage only.

today.description: Return a single UsageRecord per usage category, for today's usage only.

yearly.description: Return multple UsageRecords for each usage category, each representing usage over a yearly time-interval.

yesterday.description: Return a single UsageRecord per usage category, for yesterday's usage only.

account_sid.description: The Account that accrued the usage.

category.description: The category of usage. See Usage Categories below.

count.description: The number of usage events (e.g. the number of calls).

count_unit.description: The units in which Count is measured. For example calls for calls, messages for SMS.

description.description: A human-readable description of the usage category.

usage.description: The amount of billed usage (e.g. the number of call minutes billed for). This is frequently the same as Count, but may be different for certain usage categories like calls, where Count represents the number of calls and Usage represents the number of rounded, billed minutes.
